venue.name: Dotonbori Glico Sign (道頓堀グリコサイン)

tip.text: Sop Durian (original taste) is the best. I just wish the durian itself was much more than the ice cubes. The place is need to be cleaned all the time cause I saw people throw tissues everywhere.
I love to have Sup Kepiting Asparagus in the morning, especially when I'm having flu. Not salty but still tasty, so it's comfortable for my stomach.

formattedAddress: Kuningan City, Lt. 3 Unit 05 (Jalan Prof. Dr. Satrio Kav. 18)

tip.text: Just found a small canteen on the station. I ordered Roasted Chicken Rice for SGD 2.20, cheap and enough portion. Don't expect too much on its taste. But at least it's better than their noodle.
It has art class, movie premiere (indie), photography and exhibition gallery. Interesting, especially for art lovers and those wo want to avoid malls.
A cozy vegetarian restaurant with a touch of industrial look. The Kumbo Shitake Soup is really nice, a mix of carrot, tofu, shitake and other vegetables and soya taste. Definitely love this place.
